descriptions.name: comment-start
descriptions.message:
this `(*' is the start of a comment.
\       Hint: Did you forget spaces when writing the infix operator `( * )'?

descriptions.name: comment-not-end
descriptions.message: this is not the end of a comment.

descriptions.name: fragile-match
descriptions.description:
Fragile pattern matching: matching that will remain complete even
\      \    if additional constructors are added to one of the variant types
\      \    matched.

descriptions.name: ignored-partial-application
descriptions.description:
Partially applied function: expression whose result has function
\      \    type and is ignored.

messages.msg: label ' ^ l ^ ' was omitted in the application of this function.
labels " ^ String.concat ", " ls ^ " were omitted in the application of this function.

descriptions.name: partial-match
descriptions.description: Partial match: missing cases in pattern-matching.

descriptions.name: missing-record-field-pattern
descriptions.description: Missing fields in a record pattern.

descriptions.name: non-unit-statement
descriptions.description:
Expression on the left-hand side of a sequence that doesn't have type
\      \    "unit" (and that is not a function, see warning number 5).

descriptions.name: redundant-case
descriptions.description: Redundant case in a pattern matching (unused match case).

descriptions.name: illegal-backslash
descriptions.description: Illegal backslash escape in a string constant.

descriptions.name: bad-module-name
descriptions.description: Bad module name: the source file name is not a valid OCaml module name.

descriptions.name: unused-var
descriptions.description:
Suspicious unused variable: unused variable that is bound
\    \    with "let" or "as", and doesn't start with an underscore ("_")
\    \    character.

descriptions.name: unused-var-strict
descriptions.description:
Innocuous unused variable: unused variable that is not bound with
\    \    "let" nor "as", and doesn't start with an underscore ("_")
\    \    character.

descriptions.name: wildcard-arg-to-constant-constr
descriptions.description: Wildcard pattern given as argument to a constant constructor.

descriptions.name: eol-in-string
descriptions.description: Unescaped end-of-line in a string constant (non-portable code).

descriptions.name: duplicate-definitions
descriptions.description:
Two labels or constructors of the same name are defined in two
\      \    mutually recursive types.

descriptions.name: module-linked-twice
descriptions.description: A module is linked twice in the same executable.

descriptions.name: name-out-of-scope
descriptions.description: Constructor or label name used out of scope.

descriptions.name: disambiguated-name
descriptions.description: Disambiguated constructor or label name (compatibility warning).

descriptions.name: open-shadow-identifier
descriptions.description: Open statement shadows an already defined identifier.

descriptions.name: open-shadow-label-constructor
descriptions.description: Open statement shadows an already defined label or constructor.

descriptions.name: no-cmi-file
descriptions.description: Absent cmi file when looking up module alias.

descriptions.name: wrong-tailcall-expectation
descriptions.description: Function call annotated with an incorrect @tailcall attribute.

descriptions.name: misplaced-attribute
descriptions.description: Attribute cannot appear in this context.

descriptions.name: duplicated-attribute
descriptions.description: Attribute used more than once on an expression.

descriptions.name: unreachable-case
descriptions.description: Unreachable case in a pattern-matching (based on type information).

descriptions.name: constraint-on-gadt
descriptions.description: Type constraint on GADT type declaration.

descriptions.name: unsafe-array-syntax-without-parsing
descriptions.description: -unsafe used with a preprocessor returning a syntax tree.

descriptions.name: redefining-unit
descriptions.description: Type declaration defining a new '()' constructor.

descriptions.name: match-on-mutable-state-prevent-uncurry
descriptions.description:
Pattern-matching depending on mutable state prevents the remaining 
\      \    arguments from being uncurried.

descriptions.name: tmc-breaks-tailcall
descriptions.description: A tail call is turned into a non-tail call by the @tail_mod_cons transformation.
